STRATEGIC REASONING: {'Compute value/effort to guide counter. My values: A43(868/79), C10(780/274), C61(668/303), C55(583/388), C42(808/548), A67(822/585), B42(783/564), C43(121/84), B36(461/374). Opponent proposed these 9. Check effort: A43 79 + C10 274 =353; + C61 303=656; + C55 388=1044; + C42 548=1592; + A67 585=2177; + B42 564=2741; + C43 84=2825; + B36 374=3199. Slack 3712-3199=513 (matches their note). Total my importance sum: 868+780+668+583+808+822+783+121+461 = 5894. This is very strong for me. Check if any swaps improve within slack. My remaining items: C08(138/949 poor), A62(65/230 low), B19(262/580 middling), C73(508/976 low ROI), C67(389/578 OK), A18(484/913 low), C61 already in, etc. Best value/effort ratios left: C67 389/578; A62 65/230; B19 262/580; C73 508/976; A18 484/913; C08 138/949. With 513 slack we can only add items with effort <=513. From remaining, A62(230) fits, adds 65 importance; no-brainer? But adding requires staying under limit: 3199+230=3429 OK. Also C10 etc already in. We could also consider swapping out low-importance-for-me C43(121/84) is tiny effort and decent ratio actually. Candidates to drop to add bigger: If we wanted C67 (578) we need +578 effort but only 513 slack; we could drop C43 (84) to free to 597 and add C67 net +389-121=+268 imp and +494 effort, still within limit: 3199 -84 +578 = 3693 <=3712 OK. That gives total importance +268 compared to current. That seems strictly better for me. What about adding A62 without dropping? 3429 <= limit; adds only +65, but we can possibly do both? After swap adding C67 we are at 3693, remaining slack 19, so can't add A62. Alternatively, drop B36 (461/374) to bring room for two? If drop B36, free 374 effort and -461 importance. Could then add C67 (578) requiring net +204 effort and +389 importance change relative to drop; net -72 importance; worse. What about drop C55 (583/388) to add C67? Net -194 importance; worse. Drop C43 to add C67 is best. Also could add A62 by dropping nothing